videos.title: Spanish Food Tour - ULTIMATE FOOD TOUR in Madrid!! Best Restaurants + Tapas in Spain!!
videos.description: 🇪🇸 Ultimate Madrid Food Tour with @Spain Revealed 🥩 World’s Best Steak: https://youtu.be/FERg3aS8Y48 🔔 SUBSCRIBE: http://bit.ly/MarkWiensSubscribe Don’t miss new food videos! MADRID, SPAIN - Welcome to Madrid and today I’m hanging out with my friend @Spain Revealed from Spain Revealed, and we’re going to take you on an ultimate Spanish food tour, specifically eating dishes that are local in Madrid. From churros to snails and tapas to cocido Madrileño, get ready for the ultimate Spanish food tour in Madrid! Here are all the places we went to eat in this tour: Chocolat (https://g.page/Chocolat-Madrid?share) - We started with churros at Chocolat, one of the best places you’ll find in the city. They make them fresh and serve them with creamy chocolate. The perfect way to start a day in Madrid. La Casa del Abuelo (https://goo.gl/maps/rKw5QNi8cRon3vvD7) - Next up, James and I started with a tapas crawl, first heading to La Casa del Abuelo for their amazing shrimp cooked with garlic and olive oil in a clay pan. They are delicious, especially with some house wine. Casa Toni (https://goo.gl/maps/upxpEfSaysggDkrc8) - Next up for Casa Toni, another legendary tapas bar in Madrid, known for organ meats like pig ears on the hot plate and sweet breads. Again, a delicious friendly place, and very Madrid culture. Restaurante Casa Amadeo los Caracoles (https://goo.gl/maps/d86FSKqBEZZKjs2j7) - One of my favorite places this entire Spanish food tour in Madrid was Restaurante Casa Amadeo los Caracoles, that’s a tapas bar that specializes in snails cooked with chili and all sorts of pig parts and sausages for flavor. Amadeo the owner is 93 years old and he’s so energetic with a heart of gold. He taught us how to eat some of his favorite dishes. Posada de la Villa (https://g.page/posada-de-la-villa?share) - Next up we continued to Posada de la Villa for roasted lamb. Again legendary, and so good! Malacatín (https://g.page/Malacatin?share) - Finally to complete this food tour, there’s no way we could miss cocido Madrileño, a Madrid specialty that includes soup made from a variety of meats, with chickpeas, meats, vegetables. It’s the ultimate heavy meal comfort food and something you have to eat when you’re in Madrid. Thank you for watching and hope you enjoyed this ultimate Spanish food tour in Madrid! Thank you again to @Spain Revealed - wouldn’t have been possible without him. Go check out his channel and videos. 🎵MUSIC: https://goo.gl/HwVjdo —————————————————— 📱FOLLOW: Instagram: https://instagram.com/migrationology Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/migrationology

videos.title: What happens in your brain when you taste food | Camilla Arndal Andersen
videos.description: Visit http://TED.com to get our entire library of TED Talks, transcripts, translations, personalized Talk recommendations and more. With fascinating research and hilarious anecdotes, neuroscientist Camilla Arndal Andersen takes us into the lab where she studies people's sense of taste via brain scans. She reveals surprising insights about the way our brains subconsciously experience food -- and shows how this data could help us eat healthier without sacrificing taste. videos.title: Tasting Netherlands comfort food, part 2...I can't believe I ate this!
videos.description: Today we are tasting Dutch foods...the good and the bad, and everything in between, from comfort to what the heck is this!! Dutch food can be unique to say the least. We tried everything from raw meat to alcohol free beer. As an expat moving to the Netherlands, I never expected such a wide range of food unique to this part of the country. So you can say this is kind of a mini Dutch food review. During the Dutch food taste test there were some hits and misses but we had some fun! Life in the Netherlands as a foreigner with new food to explore has been great...If it ain't Dutch it ain't much! So here's my little living in the Netherlands vlog, I hope you enjoy it! The expat life is a great life. I CAN'T BELIEVE WE ATE THAT!!

videos.title: Part 5 of Dutch Food Tasting! Cheese, Cheese And More Cheese! Do you smell what I smell????
videos.description: As an expat coming from the US, tasting Dutch foods and be a hit or miss. If living in the Netherlands has shown us anything it's that Dutch food is anything but bland. DUTCH CHEESE can be unique to say the least but unique doesn't mean bad...smelly maybe but not bad. I never expected such a wide range of unique cheeses to this part of the country but I can tell you this, Dutch cheese is some of the best in the world. So you can say, this is kind of a mini Dutch cheese review on the smelly and not so smelly. During the Dutch food taste test there were some hits and misses but we had some fun doing it! Life in the Netherlands as a foreigner with new food to explore has been great...If it ain't Dutch it ain't much! So here's my little living in the Netherlands vlog, I hope you enjoy it! The expat life is a great life and don't be afraid to try the unique Dutch foods available to you...you won't regret it!! GET OFF THE BEATEN PATH AND EXPLORE THE DUTCH LIFE!! 0:00 Intro 2:00 Jong Belegen Boerenkaas 3:50 Oude Boerenkaas 5:07 Rookkaas 7:13 Sambalkaas 9:53 Friese Nagelkaas 12:35 Komijnekaas 17:51 Geitenkaas 19:28 Schapenkaas 21:36 Oude Rotterdamse Kaas 23:21 Oude Brokkelkaas 25:07 Brandnetelkaas 27:34 Limburgse Stinkkaas 31:33 Special Request

videos.title: Seth Rogen Taste-Tests Secret Fast-Food Burgers | The Burger Show
videos.description: Burgers are universally beloved because they're the food of the people. But few can deny the appeal of secret, off-menu burgers—a concept that was popularized by the GOAT fast-food chain, In-N-Out. With the obsessive demand for Animal-style burgers, other fast-food chains like Shake Shack and Five Guys have taken note, creating more competition in the field. So which fast-food, off-menu burger reigns supreme? Alvin is linking up with his friend and burger lover, Seth Rogen, to crown a winner. videos.title: Tasting Tabriz Kofteh, kebabs and authentic Iranian food in Tabriz Bazaar
videos.description: ► Go Follow Mark Wiens :https://www.youtube.com/c/MarkWiens ► More Street Food in Iran: https://youtu.be/6IWv7IJYNcc ►Go Follow My Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/mr.taster/ ►Music: https://mixkit.co/free-stock-music/funk/ Following Mr. Taster's and Mark Wiens' tour of Iran and their trip to the beautiful and historical city of Tabriz, we are still touring the old bazaar of Tabriz and we even tried sugar beets which was very sweet and delicious. For lunch, we went to Haj Ali in the Bazaar restaurant, which is one of the most famous restaurants in Tabriz. There have very delicious kebabs that is served with Persian rice and sumac and grilled tomatoes and it was absolutely unique combination. Then we went to Shazdeh restaurant and had Tabrizi Kofteh. One of the most original and best Tabrizi dishes, which is a combination of thigh mutton meat, chickpeas and special spices, herbs and onions, and for the middle of the kofteh, eggs, walnut kernels, plums, cherries, onions, barberry are used and it is wonderful and so delicious. ►Video By: Aref Sayad: https://www.instagram.com/arefvisualart Rambod:https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=rambod+rastegar Ali: https://www.instagram.com/alimojarad/

videos.title: Exotic THAI FOOD Tour in Bangkok with Mark Wiens! Freaky Thai Food + Yummy Face Challenge
videos.description: 🎥COLLAB ON MARK WIENS’ CHANNEL » https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CEHayLnKvwY 💗SUPPORT OUR MISSION » http://bit.ly/BestEverPatreon 🛵Learn more about Onetrip’s Vietnam tours » http://bit.ly/BEFRSOnetrip Special thanks to legendary food and travel YouTuber MARK WIENS for taking on my yummy face challenge and joining me on this exotic Bangkok food tour. Make sure to check out his latest vid, where you can watch us both eat spicy food and handle it really well. It wasn’t even that spicy. - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - » THE EXOTIC FOODS 1. TALAD KAO MARKET: Mrs. Pan’s Bug Cart ADDRESS: Soi Lat Krabang 5, Lat Krabang, Krung Thep Maha Nakhon 10520 OPEN: 2PM - 10PM  🦗The night before Mrs. Pan cooks the bugs she will later sell in the market, her son goes to Khlong Toei, Bangkok’s largest wet market, to purchase a variety of insects. She begins cooking each morning in order to make it to the market and set up her cart by 2pm. To cook the bugs, Mrs. Pan first adds oil and chopped pandan leaves to a frying pan. The pandan leaves add a nice fragrance to the bugs while cutting the bitter taste. She adds her first round of bugs and allows them to fry for roughly 30 minutes. She allows the crickets to cook for only 15 minutes. To enhance the flavors, she does not clean the pan between bugs. Then she’s off to the market, to fill hungry bellies with bugs!  💸PRICE: 1.50 USD/50 THB for Mixed Bowl of Bugs 1.20 USD/40 THB for Giant Water Bug 2. TOY KUAY TEOW: Boat Noodles (Blood Noodle Soup) ADDRESS: 15 Ratchawithi Rd, Khwaeng Thung Phaya Thai, Khet Ratchathewi, Krung Thep Maha Nakhon OPEN: 8AM - 6PM 🍜Toy Kuay Teow has been serving up boat noodles for 50 years and is on its third generation. To make one of Bangkok’s most beloved noodle soups, combine chilli dressing, pork, meatballs, vermicelli noodles, pork blood, pork soup, scallions and herbs, bok choy, fried pork skin and fried flat noodles (optional). Beef boat noodles include beef blood, rather than pork blood. 💸PRICE: .46 USD/15 THB for a small bowl .91 USD/30 THB for a normal bowl 3. J'KHAI SEAFOOD: Horseshoe Crab Eggs ADDRESS: 1300/3-4 Prachachuen Road, Bangsue Bangkok OPEN: 3PM - 12AM  J’Khai Seafood started when the owner began selling food from a small cart 34 years ago. It is now a multi-story restaurant in Bangkok, and their signature “Thai curry steamed horseshoe crab eggs” recently won Wongnai Users’ Choice for best dish.  🦀To make this tasty meal, they first steam the horseshoe crab, cutting open the lower part of the crab to remove all of the eggs. Separately, create the seasoning, mixing Thai red curry paste, sugar, MSG, oyster sauce and carnation milk. Add the seasoning to an oiled, heated pan before adding chicken egg and finger root. Allow to stir-fry for a bit, then scoop everything back into the horseshoe crab shell. Take the horseshoe crab and grill it over hot charcoal until bubbling. Top it off with coconut milk, sliced lime leaves and carrots before diving in.  💸PRICE: 15 USD/500 THB per Horseshoe Crab (may vary) - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - 💬COME SAY HI: INSTAGRAM » http://bit.ly/InstaSonnySide FACEBOOK » http://bit.ly/BEFRSFacebook 💗SUPPORT OUR MISSION: Patreon is a platform that allows people to support creators on a recurring basis. Your contribution is an investment in the creative freedom of my channel and enables me to keep my content authentic and uninterrupted. Your generous donation allows me the time and resources to create more videos for you. We also have some pretty sweet rewards, exclusive to Patreon Bestys. » http://bit.ly/BestEverPatreon 🥒ABOUT BEFRS: Hey, I’m Sonny! I’m from the US but currently call Vietnam home. I’ve been living in Asia for 10 years and started making food and travel videos to document my experiences. People either enjoyed my undeniable charm or enjoyed watching me eat things like coconut worms, and thus Best Ever Food Review Show came to be.  I travel to different parts of the world, hunting down and documenting the most unique food each country has to offer. If you see any factual food errors in my videos, please feel free to politely let me know in the comments. I'm a huge fan of trying different, interesting foods in each country. My show is from a Western point of view, but more importantly, MY point of view. It is not meant to offend any person or culture. Don’t forget to subscribe to Best Ever Food Review Show, so we can connect through food and travel and become Bestys! - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - 🎬CREDITS: DIRECTOR OF PHOTOGRAPHY » Bret Hamilton CAMERA OPERATOR » Nguyễn Tân Khải VIDEO EDITOR » Sonny PRODUCER » Huỳnh Hà My LOCAL FIXER » Sirithorn Srisarunyunont (Facebook: http://bit.ly/2ARHNyx) For business inquiries, please email: team.befrs@gmail.com

videos.description: If you are going to spend six days underground in Sardinian caves, it is best to be well prepared. Choosing the right food to keep energy and morale levels high is very important. After the food tasting the astronauts continue their underground exploration-training and tackle the art and science of cave photography. CAVES, an abbreviation of Cooperative Adventure for Valuing and Exercising human behaviour and performance Skills, prepares astronauts to work safely and effectively and solve problems as a multicultural team while exploring uncharted areas following space procedures. Credits: ESA­--V. Crobu and S. Sechi

videos.title: Krakow Poland - Fun, Food and The Worlds's BEST Vodka tasting!
videos.description: Krakow Poland is one of the most beautiful cities in Europe! In this video we explore Krakow's street food, castle and try some of the best vodka in the world. Krakow has some famous street food, so we try Obwarzanek which is a Polish street bagel.  We eat some fine dining with wild boar and mountain trout, we then try some of Poland's best vodka! Come along for some fun, food and castle views in Krakow Poland. This video was filmed in October 2021, as the final city on our Euro Trip.  A Couple of Nomads?  About Us Well, we are a couple from worlds apart that has chosen Valencia, Spain to be our home base. Vicky is born and raised in Seoul, South Korea, now an American citizen. Josh is an American, well, born and raised in small town, Ohio.  We left our jobs, family and friends and moved to Valencia, Spain in the middle of the pandemic. We decided to that we should also start a YouTube channel to show the world that, you can do anything (even if you are getting grey hair), if you think you can! If you want to see how a couple of expats can live the Mediterranean dream, and you want to join us on our journey...then subscribe, we would love to have you as part of our extended family! Cheers! Vicky u0026 Josh  #Krakow #Poland #StreetFood #Europe #ACoupleOfNomads

videos.title: The Best Tasting Immune Boosting Popsicles Ever
videos.description: Our immune system works tirelessly to keep us safe during cold and flu season. So it’s always important to get a daily dose of vitamins and minerals. This easy to make popsicle is an excellent source to get the vitamins and nutrients your body needs but in a great tasting and enjoyable way. Good boosting your immunity for both parents and children.  Recipe: 2 Oranges Ginger 1/2 Lemon 4 Carrots 1 piece Turmeric 1 tsp Honey What makes this drink beneficial? Vitamin A, found in orange, aids in the production of new white blood cells, the immune cells that travel through your circulation in search of and eliminate viruses that might be detrimental to you.  Ginger's anti-inflammatory qualities aid in immune system stimulation.  Lemon, on the other hand, is packed with Vitamin C which assists in antimicrobial action by improving the operation of what is known as natural killer cells, which help to remove infections Anthocyanin, a compound found in purple carrots can help reduce inflammation.  Carrots and honey contain lots of vitamin A, which aids in the production of white blood cells known as T-cells that shields the body against cancer-causing cells.  One of the compounds that may be found in turmeric is called curcumin, and it is known to have anti-inflammatory qualities that can help enhance immunity.  Remember, a healthy immune system also requires an active lifestyle. It’s never too late to start! videos.title: MUST-TRY Croatian Food Tour in Istria, Croatia 🇭🇷 Pula, Rovinj, & Motovun Road Trip!
videos.description: Watch Next: 24 Hours in Zagreb, Croatia ► https://youtu.be/wQXxBYAsKNc Watch Next: My First Day in Russia ► https://youtu.be/LopAn_cq1B4 More Information about this episode👇 Istria County, Croatia - Pula, Rovinj, and Motovun; three incredible destinations on the Istrian Peninsula of Croatia. The western coast of Croatia is home to the beautiful region of Istria, which is often overlooked by Croatian tourists. Check out Goran's Channel: https://youtu.be/kHykb6QXtDg After leaving the capital of Zagreb, we set out on our Croatian road trip, and our first stop was Pula. Luckily, we had a wonderful local Croatian friend Renata, to take us around the Pula Arena and give a quick tour of Pula. We eat a traditional Croatian lunch, and enjoy some delicious gelato before having to leave Pula for Rovinj. Renata's Watercolor workshops in Pula: https://www.airbnb.com/experiences/1710182 From Pula, we checked into our accommodation in Rovinjsko Selo, nearby the popular Rovinj, Croatia, and then drove into Rovinj for sunset. Rovinj is such a beautiful little city. It is also more popular for travelers than Pula. The next morning, we leave Rovinj for Motovun to experience an Istria Food Tour around the amazing Istrian countryside with Eat Istria ( https://eatistria.com). Our day started at the foothills of Motovun; a fairytale-like village in Istria. We started at Mira Tartufi farm, before heading out into the Istrian forest to hunt for truffles! Miro Tartufi (Truffle Farm) - http://miro-tartufi.com/en/ After the first leg of our Istria food tour, we leave Motovun and drive through the Istrian countryside to try some delicious and overwhelming, haha, goat cheeses! Kumparicka Goat Farm - https://www.kumparicka.com/en/home Finally, we finish our Istria food tour with lunch at a traditional Croatian Konoba - or local farm-to-table tavern. We try fresh pasta and meats that are 100% from this farm. Amazing! Konoba "DOMA" - https://konoba-doma.business.site We finish the day back in Rovinj for sunset again. I join my local friend Ella for more delicious gelato at her favorite spot right in the heart of Rovinj old town and then we hangout along the coast. Gelateria I Nonni (Rovinj) - https://www.facebook.com/inonnicroatia/ We cap off an amazing experience her in Istria with a swim in the Adriatic Sea. This region of Croatia is absolutely incredible. I hope you enjoyed this "Best Things to do in the Istria Region of Croatia" video ❤️ If so, please hit that "👍" button, and leave a comment! Otherwise, see ya next week from our Croatian Road Trip!!! 🔔 PLEASE SUBSCRIBE, for more food u0026 travel vlogs ► https://bit.ly/you-da-best​​​​ ---------- WATCH ANOTHER "TRAVEL DEEPER" SERIES: ✈️ Russia ► https://bit.ly/Travel-Deeper-Russia-Series Philippines ► https://bit.ly/Travel-Deeper-Philippines-Series Japan ► https://bit.ly/Travel-Deeper-Japan-Series Brazil ► https://bit.ly/Travel-Deeper-Brazil-Series Australia ► https://bit.ly/Travel-Deeper-Australia-Series USA ► https://bit.ly/Travel-Deeper-USA-Series Mexico ► https://bit.ly/Travel-Deeper-Mexico-Series ---------- WHO AM I? Hi! My name is Gareth Leonard, an American Travel YouTuber with a passion for slow, meaningful Travel. I have spent the past 13+ years traveling around the world while creating travel vlogs to help inspire and educate people to “Travel Deeper.” If you enjoy my work, please subscribe to this channel and turn on the notifications bell to stay up-to-date with my travel deeper adventures. Daily updates can also be found on my Instagram Stories (@traveldeeper), so if you’ve read this far, send me a DM with the “🦊” emoji so I know you’re a real one! videos.title: Tasting POPULAR PULAOS At ULAVACHARU Hyderabad|Andhra, Telangana Food|RAJU GARI PULAO|BAMBOO CHICKEN
videos.description: #BiryaniLovers #HyderabadFoodTrail #GourmetOnTheRoad  Andhra,Telangana, Rayalseema food at Ulavacharu, Hyderabad. Pulao and biryanis in Hyderabad. Pulao restaurants in Hyderabad. Raju Gari Pulao, Rayala Vari Kodi Pulao. This hugely popular establishment in Hyderabad is famous for its unique takes on traditional recipes. Their specialties are their biryanis or rather, their pulaos, of which they make 18 varieties! And each of them has its own unique flavour and character. Food Lovers' Editor, Kripal Amanna joins Ravitej Ravuri of StreetByte on an epic pulao tasting session. He tastes a couple of unconventional starters namely, the Bamboo Chicken, an appetiser of chicken cooked in a bamboo stalk in a tandoor, and the Bangla Kodi. From their wide menu of pulaos, he tries the unique Raju Gari Pulao, a vegetarian Guthivankaya Pulao with eggplant, as well as the Rayala Vary Kodi Pulao with gongura leaves. He rounds off the meal with an indulgent rose milk and a sweet pudding called Junnu made from colostrum.  GOURMET ON THE ROAD RATING  BAMBOO CHICKEN this chicken is cooked in a fresh, tangy herb marinade and steamed in a bamboo shell. the masala has penetrated all the way into the chicken. the meat is juicy but a wee bit powdery in its texture. rs. 445 8/10 BANGLA KODI an interesting appetiser of chicken encased in a thick slice of potato that is marinated in a red spice paste and deep fried. almost resembles a mini taco! the slightly underdone potato adds a textural crunch. rs. 399 8.5/10 RAJU GARI KODI PULAO this is unlike any biryani/ pulao i have ever tasted! the consistency is that of a khichdi or rice and gravy mixed together. the pulao is flavoured with pepper, whole spices and green chilli takes some getting used to, the chicken is here just to support the flavourful rice. rs 335 9/10 GUTHIVANKAYA PULAO a refreshing take on a vegetarian pulao or biryani. this masaledar pulao has an eggplant gravy ladled on the rice. the eggplant adds a meaty bite to the dish. rs 285 8/10 RAYALA VARI KODI PULAO cooked with a masala made of sorrel leaves/ sour spinach or gongura as it is popularly known in the region, this pulao is unique in its flavours. you taste the sour notes in the rich masala and chicken. rs 345 8.5/10 RAJAHMUNDRY ROSE MILK thick, rich milk infused with a sweet rose syrup. difficult to down an entire glass! rs 125 8/10 JUNNU this milk pudding is rich and creamy. visualise lightly sweetened khova in a custard form. rs 95 8/10 ADDRESS: Ulavacharu, 2-1/6 u0026 2-1/6/A, 1st Floor, 133, Fantasy Square Building, Old Mumbai Highway, Opposite Nissan Showroom, Biodiversity Circle, Gachibowli, Jayabheri Pine Valley, Gachibowli, Hyderabad, Telangana 500032 LOCATION TAG: https://maps.app.goo.gl/GFumXpewuFDYcrpM6 SUPPORT FOOD LOVERS https://www.patreon.com/foodloverstv  Our vision at Food Lovers is to be India’s finest, foremost and most importantly, trusted content platform in the field of food, wine u0026 spirits and dining. videos.title: Part 3 of Dutch Food Tasting! The good, the bad and the "give that to me again."!
videos.description: As an expat coming from the US, tasting Dutch foods and be a hit or miss. If living in the Netherlands has shown us anything it's that Dutch food is anything but bland. 3 fieldtrips , 7 foods and 3.5 Lbs. gained, I can honestly tell you it's anything but bland. I never expected such a wide range of food unique to this part of the country. So you can say this is kind of a mini Dutch food review. During the Dutch food taste test there were some hits and misses but we had some fun! Life in the Netherlands as a foreigner with new food to explore has been great...If it ain't Dutch it ain't much! So here's my little living in the Netherlands vlog, I hope you enjoy it! The expat life is a great life.

videos.title: World Famous Hyderabadi CHICKEN BIRYANI | Biryani MAKING & Tasting
videos.description: ► More Street Food in Hyderabad: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Kt3mt2ZbMjEu0026list=PLDs8Vu-e-HxLRxcd7bLZA8MD44u9gLxLJu0026index=1 ► Subscribe to Delhi Food Walks: https://www.youtube.com/user/Delhifoodwalks The Hyderabadi Biryani needs no detailed introduction. This glorious delicacy is a staple for the locals and the go-to dish for the tourists. Hyderabadi Biryani is characteristically distinct from its popular counterparts because of its distinct aroma, taste, texture and the mode of preparation. With the essence of Turkish, Mughlai and Arabic influences in it, the Hyderabadi Biryani has been an integral part of the Hyderabad’s culinary tradition since a long time. In this culinary exploration, we have set out to savour the dazzling aura of this majestic dish at some of the most famed destinations across the city. We are happy to be accompanied by our gracious host Sankalp Vishnu who is an acclaimed food critic and food expert. We tried Hyderabadi biryani at two eminent places-The Lucky restaurant and the Bawarchi restaurant. Our intention was to understand the nuances or fine tuning of the variations in the Hyderabadi biryani as adopted by these joints.  Our first stop was the Lucky restaurant that serves one of the best versions of the Kachi Gost Ki Biryani. We got the opportunity to witness the making of a batch of Hyderabadi Biryani at their wonderful, aromatic kitchen. The seemingly easy procedure entails an astute understanding of the dynamics of its cooking, perseverance and dexterity. The genial owner for Lucky restaurant walked us through the process sharing all the details of their prized preparation. We then tried the Nalli Biryani along with some other delectable meaty wonders. The feast ended with the lusciously amazing Khubani ka Meetha a dessert that’s exclusive to the city. The next day we went to the acclaimed Bawarchi restaurant to try their version of the Hyderabadi Biryani. In recent years it has emerged as favourite destination for the same. The beautifully done Chicken Biryani was worth all the reputation. It ticked all the boxes of parameters that make the magic of a biryani work. A distinct feature of the biryani here was the pleasantly notable presence of the shah jeera flavour in it. Here we also tried the Hyderabad famous Double Ka Meetha and the Kaddu ka kheer. The latter one was the best.  While winding up this Hyderabadi biryani trail we couldn’t but wonder at the flamboyant stature of this apparently royal dish that rules the heart of the masses in and beyond this city.  We are truly grateful to Sankalp Vishnu for his cooperation. WORLD FAMOUS Hyderabadi Haleem | HALEEM Making u0026 Tasting in Hyderabad https://youtu.be/cnxcE2Lr6B0 #biryanimaking #HyderabadFoodTour  About the host - Anubhav Sapra: Anubhav Sapra is an avid foodie! He is a Founder but proudly calls himself a Foodie-in-chief at Delhi Food Walks. He is also a street-food and Indian regional cuisine connoisseur and loves to write about street-food. To know more, visit www.anubhavsapra.com  Please subscribe to our YouTube channel to keep our Indian street food explorations video in your feed!  Thank you for watching!
